No, man! Al, there's no other way!
You gotta believe me.

958
01:14:11,200 --> 01:14:14,300
I believe you.
I just don't want you to get hurt.

959
01:14:14,700 --> 01:14:19,800
Look, I know this looks bad.
Al, man, I'm not a screwup on this one.

960
01:14:19,700 --> 01:14:22,400
I've got proof this time. Real proof.

961
01:14:23,300 --> 01:14:26,300
(Al) But the election's over. It's history.

962
01:14:26,300 --> 01:14:28,900
Like you're gonna be
if you don't put that gun down.

963
01:14:28,800 --> 01:14:31,300
Al, please!

964
01:14:32,100 --> 01:14:36,000
If you love me like a brother,
you gotta back me up on this.

965
01:14:35,900 --> 01:14:39,600
All right, Mike. I'll back you up.
What do you want me to do?

966
01:14:39,600 --> 01:14:41,900
Just let me explain what happened.

967
01:14:42,800 --> 01:14:45,200
- Oh!
- (crowd scream)

968
01:14:45,700 --> 01:14:49,800
That's it. Game over.
I'm not even getting paid for this.

969
01:14:49,900 --> 01:14:53,300
- This is not worth it.
- Look out. Look out. Look out.

970
01:14:53,300 --> 01:14:55,200
OK.

971
01:14:55,900 --> 01:14:58,000
(crowd scream)

972
01:14:58,200 --> 01:15:02,700
Mr Thunder-maker here is gonna start
barkin' fire if you don't stop moving

973
01:15:02,600 --> 01:15:05,200
and listen to what
this young man has to say.

974
01:15:05,800 --> 01:15:07,800
Go ahead, Mike. Clear.

975
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:12,800
Thank you, sir. You've just met Drake
Sabitch, a great American soldier.

976
01:15:12,700 --> 01:15:16,100
I'd like to tell you about
some other great American soldiers.

977
01:15:16,000 --> 01:15:18,600
Drake Sabitch's grandfather,
Winston Sabitch,

978
01:15:18,500 --> 01:15:21,600
whose name you'll find
at the top of this list.

979
01:15:21,600 --> 01:15:26,700
It says that he registered
and voted for Governor Tracy.

980
01:15:26,600 --> 01:15:29,800
- We're proud to have him as a voter.
- Hold your tongue, wench.

981
01:15:29,700 --> 01:15:34,000
The fact is Winston Sabitch was killed
in the Argonne Forest in 1918.

982
01:15:33,900 --> 01:15:38,200
A zeppelin landed on his head,
smashing his head clean out of his ass.

983
01:15:38,200 --> 01:15:41,300
That's my granddad. Rest in pieces, sir.

984
01:15:42,400 --> 01:15:46,100
Norris Sabitch met his maker
in Iwo Jima, 1944.

985
01:15:46,300 --> 01:15:51,000
Nelson Sabitch was killed
near the 38th Parallel in Korea.

986
01:15:50,900 --> 01:15:55,900
But yesterday these men managed
to cast their vote for Evelyn Tracy.

987
01:15:55,800 --> 01:15:58,300
(disapproving murmurs)

988
01:15:58,300 --> 01:16:00,800
You heard it here, folks. Voter fraud.

989
01:16:04,800 --> 01:16:08,800
Half these people are buried in the
Garfield cemetery. That's one county.

990
01:16:08,800 --> 01:16:13,500
- It's probably the same statewide.
- Hold on just a minute, young fellow.

991
01:16:13,400 --> 01:16:17,500
There's a perfectly good explanation
for all of this. Neuschwander.

992
01:16:18,200 --> 01:16:24,100
Actually, there is a perfectly
good explanation for this.

993
01:16:24,300 --> 01:16:27,300
- She put us up to it.
- Would you shut up?!

994
01:16:27,300 --> 01:16:29,100
- It's all her.
- Shut up!

995
01:16:32,400 --> 01:16:35,800
Ladies and gentlemen,
this young man is a fine patriot.

996
01:16:35,700 --> 01:16:38,400
He deserves to be hoisted up
on our shoulders.

997
01:16:38,400 --> 01:16:41,100
- Sergeant, please. This isn't necessary.
- Come on.

998
01:16:41,000 --> 01:16:43,500
- Oh, you're a large American.
- Argh!

999
01:16:45,700 --> 01:16:47,600
Get off of me.

1000
01:16:48,400 --> 01:16:52,200
My foot's caught a little bit.
I'm sorry. I beg your pardon.

1001
01:16:52,200 --> 01:16:56,400
- I'm asking you to get off me!
- Governor... I should say ex-governor!

1002
01:16:56,300 --> 01:16:59,200
I'm just trying to get
a little leverage on my foot.

1003
01:16:59,200 --> 01:17:01,100
Agh!

1004
01:17:03,400 --> 01:17:07,200
- No, no, no! Please, somebody help me!
- Oh, man.

1005
01:17:07,100 --> 01:17:09,200
(grunting)

1006
01:17:11,100 --> 01:17:15,400
- OK. Hi, how are ya?
- Somebody get him off of me!

1007
01:17:16,000 --> 01:17:18,000
For God's sakes.

1008
01:17:18,000 --> 01:17:19,900
(grunting continues)

1009
01:17:19,900 --> 01:17:22,800
Shut up! Shut up!

1010
01:17:28,100 --> 01:17:33,400
Thanks, bro. At times in the campaign
I lost sight of what really mattered.

1011
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:36,900
- I never should have doubted you.
- Oh, thanks, man. It's cool.

1012
01:17:36,900 --> 01:17:39,300
Are you sure
you don't want a job on my staff?

1013
01:17:40,100 --> 01:17:44,200
You know what, Al? I don't think
I'm really cut out for politics.

1014
01:17:44,200 --> 01:17:47,000
Besides, I gotta rebuild that rec centre.

1015
01:17:46,800 --> 01:17:49,800
- The kids really love the place, so...
- Yeah, I know.

1016
01:17:49,800 --> 01:17:53,800
Hey, I got somebody you gotta meet.
Scott, come here a second.

1017
01:17:56,200 --> 01:17:59,700
Check this kid out. He's got an arm
like you used to have. Hey, Scott.

1018
01:17:59,700 --> 01:18:02,900
Hey. Mr Governor,
can I please have your autograph?

1019
01:18:02,900 --> 01:18:05,600
Why not? Governor elect.

1020
01:18:05,700 --> 01:18:07,600
Get it right, moron.

1021
01:18:09,100 --> 01:18:10,600
- There you go.
- Wow.

1022
01:18:10,600 --> 01:18:13,700
Check this out.
Gimme a toss, Scott. Hey, buddy.

1023
01:18:13,700 --> 01:18:15,600
Ooh!

1024
01:18:15,500 --> 01:18:19,300
Nice toss, Scott.
Oh, man, the kid's got a cannon.

1025
01:18:19,200 --> 01:18:21,400
- Go long.
- OK.

1026
01:18:22,100 --> 01:18:24,100
- Ow!
- Oh!

1027
01:18:24,100 --> 01:18:26,600
- I'm sorry, ma'am.
- You OK?

1028
01:18:32,700 --> 01:18:35,500
- So long, little brother.
- OK. See you, Al.

1029
01:18:38,100 --> 01:18:42,300
- So this is it, huh, Steve?
- I guess I'm gonna miss you.

1030
01:18:42,300 --> 01:18:46,100
I'm not gonna miss a 9mm to my head,
but... What were you thinking?

1031
01:18:45,900 --> 01:18:48,200
I don't know.

1032
01:18:52,100 --> 01:18:55,600
All right, you guys.
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

1033
01:19:00,600 --> 01:19:03,900
Oh, my God! No! No!

1034
01:19:03,800 --> 01:19:05,900
Please don't take off!

1035
01:19:06,000 --> 01:19:07,800
Please!

1036
01:19:07,800 --> 01:19:10,200
Al! Al! No! No!

1037
01:19:10,200 --> 01:19:12,300
(Mike screaming)

